node.title: Live updates: Auckland and other red areas turn orange, more Dimension close contact test results due back
node.description: All the latest on New Zealand's COVID-19 outbreak and Omicron threat.
node.content: ["There were 60 new COVID-19 infections in New Zealand on Thursday - but fears over an Omicron outbreak were kept at bay for now, with just one more Omicron case detected who had been active in the community.", "That second case - unrelated to the infection of British DJ Dimension - was an Air New Zealand crew member. No locations of interest have been identified yet, and seven close contacts have returned negative tests so far.", "New Zealand will discover today if any of the close contacts of Dimension (AKA Robert Etheridge) who were still awaiting their COVID-19 test results have tested positive.", "It comes as every area that was at the red setting of the traffic light system - barring Northland - moved to orange overnight. That includes Auckland, Taup\u014d, Rotorua lakes districts, Whakat\u0101ne, Kawerau, \u014cp\u014dtiki, Gisborne, Wairoa, Rangit\u012bkei, Whanganui and Ruapehu.", "COVID-19 test results of many more of Dimension's close and casual contacts expected back today.", "One more close contact test result due back for Air NZ crew member.", "Auckland and every other area that was at the red traffic light - barring Northland - moved to orange at 11:59pm last night.", "There were 60 new community Delta infections on Thursday - 20 in Auckland, 28 in Waikato, eight in Bay of Plenty and one each in Lakes, Tair\u0101whiti and Canterbury.", "On Thursday, 44 patients were in hospitals with Delta - seven of whom were in ICU.", "Click here for all locations of interest.", "6:45am:"]
